============================================================
THE 2-1-0 STRUCTURE: WINNER-DRAW-LOSER LAYERS
============================================================

Witness w categories relative to pair (u,v):
  2-winner: w beats both u and v (common predecessor of u,v)
  0-loser: w loses to both u and v (common successor of u,v)
  1-mixer: w beats one, loses to other

FUNDAMENTAL THEOREM:
  For pair (u,v) with arc u->v:
  sigma(u,v) = #{w: w beats both u,v} + #{w: w loses to both u,v}
  lambda(u,v) = #{w: (w->u, v->w) forming 3-cycle v->w->u->v}
  delta(u,v) = #{w: (u->w, w->v) forming transitive u->w->v}

  The 3 categories (sigma, lambda, delta) = (extremal, cyclic, transitive)
  partition all n-2 witnesses of each pair.

  Vitali atoms shift weight from 'transitive' to 'cyclic' (or vice versa)
  for SX pairs, while preserving the extremal count... wait, no!
  Since sigma changes by +-1 and lambda is preserved,
  delta changes by -/+1. So the TRANSFER is between sigma and delta:
  extremal <-> transitive, NOT cyclic!

  This means Vitali atoms convert TRANSITIVE witnesses into EXTREMAL witnesses
  (or vice versa) for SX pairs, leaving CYCLIC witnesses unchanged.

